### PHASE 6: Create Implementation Plan

**Goal:** Translate architecture decision into concrete steps, including how to validate it works.

**Plan Format:**

```
IMPLEMENTATION PLAN: [Feature/System Name]

PREREQUISITES:
- Skill 1: Team needs [knowledge/tool]
  → Mitigation: [Training/hiring/spike work]
- Skill 2: ...

MILESTONE 1: [2-week]
Objective: [Concrete goal]
Tasks:
  - Subtask 1.1: [Specific, measurable]
  - Subtask 1.2: [Specific, measurable]
Validation:
  - [Test case] passes
  - [Performance benchmark] meets target

MILESTONE 2: [2-week]
Objective: ...

RISKS & HANDLING:
- Risk 1: [What could go wrong]
  → Early signal: [How we detect it early]
  → Mitigation: [What we do about it]

GO/NO-GO CRITERIA:
- ✓ [Metric 1] meets target
- ✓ [Metric 2] meets target
- ✓ [Health check 1] passes
→ If any fail: [Rollback plan] or [Fix plan]

MONITORING & OBSERVABILITY:
- Metric 1: [What we measure]
  ├─ Alert if > [threshold]
  └─ Dashboard: [Location]
- Metric 2: ...

TIMELINE TO PRODUCTION:
- Week 1-2: Development
- Week 3: Integration testing
- Week 4: Load testing + ops review
- Week 5: Deploy to staging
- Week 6: Canary (10% of traffic) for 3 days
- Week 7: Full rollout (if canary healthy)
```

**Example plan:**

```
IMPLEMENTATION PLAN: Async Email Delivery

PREREQUISITES:
- Knowledge: Team understands message queues
  → Mitigation: 2-hour spike on RabbitMQ basics
- Infra: RabbitMQ cluster available
  → Mitigation: Ops team provisions staging environment

MILESTONE 1 (Weeks 1-2): Build Email Queue Adapter
Objective: Refactor EmailService to use queue, no production change yet
Tasks:
  - Design EmailJob message format + versioning
  - Implement QueuedEmailService (wrapper around old service)
  - Add integration tests (EmailJob → actual email sent)
  - Add consumer app that reads queue + sends emails
Validation:
  ✓ 10k emails sent through queue in load test
  ✓ Consumer restarts without losing emails (durability)
  ✓ Consumer can process 100 emails/sec (throughput target)

MILESTONE 2 (Weeks 3-4): Switch 10% of Traffic
Objective: Validate in production with real email workload
Tasks:
  - Deploy consumer service to production
  - Wrap UserService.sendVerificationEmail() to check feature flag
  - Feature flag sends 10% to queue, 90% to old synchronous path
  - Monitor dead-letter queue daily
Validation:
  ✓ 99.9% of emails delivered within SLA (same as before)
  ✓ Queue depth stays under 1000 (not backing up)
  ✓ Consumer CPU stays under 30%
  ✓ ZERO lost emails (queue + dead-letter monitoring)

MILESTONE 3 (Week 5): Gradual Rollout
Objective: Move to 100% async by monitoring error rates
Tasks:
  - Week 5: Move to 50% async
  - Week 6: Move to 90% async (old path still there for safety)
  - Week 7: Move to 100% async (remove old path)
Validation:
  ✓ Each step: Email delivery metrics stable for 24 hours
  ✓ No increase in spam complaints
  ✓ Bounce rate unchanged

RISKS & HANDLING:
Risk: RabbitMQ cluster goes down
  → Early signal: Queue consumer can't connect (monitored alert)
  → Mitigation: Feature flag switches back to synchronous (1-min fix)
           Ops team pages for RabbitMQ restart (standard playbook)

Risk: Old email service bugs now delayed (harder to debug)
  → Early signal: Dead-letter queue growing
  → Mitigation: Inspect dead-letter queue daily, fix bugs immediately
           Keep old consumer running even when 100% async

Risk: Message format versioning nightmare
  → Early signal: Consumer crashes on unexpected message fields
  → Mitigation: Validate message schema at publish time
           Version messages explicitly, handle old versions gracefully

GO/NO-GO CRITERIA:
Before moving from Milestone 1 → 2:
  ✓ 10k load test completes with zero failures
  ✓ Consumer restarts 5x without losing emails
  ✓ Latency < 100ms end-to-end (original target)
  ✓ Code review approved by 2 senior engineers

Before moving to 100% async:
  ✓ Metrics stable at 50% for 7 days
  ✓ Customer complaints unchanged (no increase in missing emails)
  ✓ On-call team comfortable with monitoring

MONITORING & OBSERVABILITY:
Metric: Email delivery latency
  ├─ Alert if > 10 seconds (99th percentile)
  ├─ Dashboard: Metrics / Email Delivery

Metric: Queue depth
  ├─ Alert if > 10,000 messages (consumer can't keep up)
  ├─ Dashboard: Infra / Queue Health

Metric: Dead-letter queue size
  ├─ Alert if > 0 (manual review required)
  ├─ Dashboard: Infra / Queue Health

TIMELINE TO PRODUCTION:
Week 1-2: Milestone 1 (local + staging testing)
Week 3-4: Milestone 2 (10% production)
Week 5-7: Milestone 3 (gradual rollout)
Week 8: Decommission old synchronous path
Week 9: Retrospective + lessons learned
```

