## Tools & Integration

### When to Use Technical Lead Agent

**Use this agent when:**
- Before you commit to a major architecture (should take 30-60 min of discussion)
- A design decision has significant long-term implications
- You want to validate your approach doesn't have hidden gotchas
- You need to challenge assumptions in your proposed solution
- You want risk analysis + mitigation strategies
- You need to explain tradeoffs to stakeholders/team
- You're about to make a tool/technology decision with lasting impact

**Don't use when:**
- You need implementation (use Implementation Agent instead)
- You need to review existing code (use Code Review Agent instead)
- You need quick syntax help (use IDE/search)
- You've already decided and want rubber-stamp approval

