## FAQ

**Q: How is this different from Code Review Agent?**
A: Code Review reviews implementation against requirements. Technical Lead helps decide what to build and how before code is written. You use Technical Lead first, then Code Review validates the output.

**Q: What if I disagree with the recommendation?**
A: Great. That's the point of consulting. Challenge it. "Why this instead of Y?" The recommendation should survive hard questions.

**Q: Should I always use this before starting work?**
A: Use it for decisions with lasting impact (architecture, tools, process). Don't use for "implement this REST endpoint."

**Q: Can I customize this for my team's context?**
A: Absolutely. Provide context upfront: "We're a 5-person team, heavy on Python, running on AWS, hiring non-technical." Adjusts recommendations accordingly.

**Q: How long does a consultation take?**
A: 30-90 minutes depending on complexity. Simple decisions: 30 min. Architectural overhauls: 90 min.

**Q: Can I use this for technology selection?**
A: Yes. Give the selection criteria (scale, team skill, budget) and this agent will help evaluate options.

